channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: WNBA Player A’ja Wilson Gets Shoe Endorsement Deal, Has a Fit Because Caitlin Clark Got One First
Contentious primaries in 3 states set up crucial general election matchups in House, Senate - What to know
item.description: Contentious primaries Tuesday in Maryland, West Virginia and Nebraska will set up crucial general election showdowns this autumn in the battles for the House and Senate.

item.title: Biden Sharply Hiking Tariffs on Chinese EVs, Solar Cells, Steel
item.description: The Biden administration announced plans to slap new tariffs on Chinese electric vehicles, advanced batteries, solar cells, steel, aluminum and medical equipment - an election-year move that's likely to increase friction between the world's two largest economies.

item.title: Red Bull Wingsuit Flyers Sail THROUGH London’s Iconic Tower Bridge in Spectacular Video
White House walks diplomatic tightrope on Israel amid contradictory messaging: 'You can't have it both ways'
item.description: The Biden administration continues to take criticism for its stances on Israel, which some critics have called contradictory.

item.title: Gov. DeSantis: Wife Casey Won't Seek Office
item.description: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis quashed rumors of his wife's political ambitions, asserting during a Monday press conference that Casey DeSantis has "zero" interest in running for office, citing her aversion to the "nonsense" of politics.

item.title: Kash Patel: Senior Military Officials Intentionally Delayed National Guard Deployment on January 6th
NY v Trump: Prosecutors to resume questioning Michael Cohen after testimony on Stormy Daniels payment
item.description: Prosecutors to continue questioning Michael Cohen on Tuesday after the ex-Trump attorney took the stand Monday to testify against former President Trump in his criminal trial.

item.title: Jesse Binnall to Newsmax: Trump's Civil Rights Violated
item.description: Jesse Binnall, an attorney for former President Donald Trump, told Newsmax on Monday that the latest flub by the prosecution in the business records case in New York is another example of the former president's civil rights being violated.

item.title: New Report on Medicare Solvency Showcases Fairytale Accounting Xavier Becerra and Julie Su Are Known For
Michael Cohen, corroborating others, says Trump wanted to silence Stormy because of the election
item.description: American lawyer Michael Cohen's testimony Monday told a familiar story: an attempt to confirm the account of the National Enquirer’s publisher.

item.title: Donald Trump Jr. to Newsmax: 'Level of Corruption' Never Seen Before
item.description: Americans see everything the Biden White House and the Democratic Party are throwing at former President Donald Trump in the cases being brought against him in heavily Democrat areas, Donald Trump Jr. told Newsmax on Monday.

item.title: Monday in Manhattan: Prosecution's 'Star' Witness, Michael Cohen, Takes the Stand (Trump Trial - Day 16)
Nevada Supreme Court rejects teachers union-backed appeal to put A's public funding on '24 ballot
item.description: A proposed ballot initiative, which would let voters choose whether to repeal public funding approved last year for a new MLB stadium, has been struck down by the Nevada Supreme Court.

item.title: Karoline Leavitt to Newsmax: Trump N.Y. Trial 'Waste of Time'
item.description: Karoline Leavitt, the national press secretary for Donald Trump's presidential campaign, said testimony by Michael Cohen during Trump's criminal trial in New York proved again what a "sham" and "waste of time" the prosecution of the former president has been.
